<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Ex-Saints PR Director Dead at 69 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- Jerry Wynn, a former public relations  
director for the New Orleans Saints and the San Diego Chargers, has 
died at the age of 69. 
</P>
<P>
	Wynn died Wednesday of complications following cancer surgery.  
</P>
<P>
	After 12 years as public relations director for the Chargers, he  
moved to New Orleans in 1977 and took the same job with the Saints. 
</P>
<P>
	``Jerry was the consummate artist in his field,'' said Don  
Weiss, former NFL executive director. ``He was always upbeat and 
had a great knack at dealing with all facets of the media. Because 
of this, the league used his expertise for the first Super Bowl in 
Los Angeles.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Wynn also was sports manager for the 1984 world's fair in New  
Orleans, a media consultant for CBS Sports, a public relations 
instructor at Loyola University, a publicity director for the Fair 
Grounds race track and a public relations consultant for the city 
of New Orleans. 
</P>
<P>
	He coordinated media transportation for Pope John Paul II's  
visit to New Orleans in 1987 and was a member of the Host Committee 
for the Republican National Convention in New Orleans in 1988. 
</P>
<P>
	Survivors include his wife, Bobby Wynn, two daughters, a son, a  
sister and four grandchildren. 
</P>
<P>
	A memorial service was scheduled for Sunday at Touro Synagogue  
in New Orleans. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
