<CATEGORY> washington </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Clinton Home Seller Supported GOP </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- With President and Mrs. Clinton the happy  
buyers of a five-bedroom Dutch Colonial house in a wooded New York 
City suburb, you'd think the first family would be pleased to learn 
the dwelling's seller is a political contributor. 
</P>
<P>
	The problem is he gave money to Republicans.  
</P>
<P>
	Dr. Jeffrey Weisberg, who with his wife Cheryl is selling the  
Clintons the $1.7 million home in Chappaqua, Westchester County, 
donated $3,500 to the New York Republican County Committee in 1996, 
according to the Federal Election Commission. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
