<P>
	In Washington, a spokeswoman for the U.S. Navy's Military  
Sealift Command said the USNS Kilauea, an ammunition supply ship, 
was standing by as an alternative helicopter landing facility for 
any emergency operation. 
</P>
<P>
	In another development, Nobel peace laureate Jose Ramos Horta  
flew to the United States today to urge world donors to freeze all 
aid to Indonesia to punish it for allegedly supporting the 
anti-independence militias. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
