<HEADLINE> Phillies' Prince Activated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Catcher Tom Prince, who had been on the  
disabled list since spring training, was activated Friday by the 
Philadelphia Phillies, who also brought up two players from the 
minors. 
</P>
<P>
	Prince injured his left wrist during spring training and had  
surgery in April. 
</P>
<P>
	Infielder Torey Lovullo's contract was purchased from  
Scranton/Wilkes-Barre. Lovullo hit .280 in 136 games, and his 106 
RBIs set a Red Barons' record. 
</P>
<P>
	Philadelphia recalled right-handed reliever Cliff Politte from  
Reading, where he was 9-8 with a 3.63 ERA. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
