<HEADLINE> Europe: Dollar, Gold Both Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- The U.S. dollar was mixed against other major  
currencies in European trading today. Gold prices also were mixed. 
</P>
<P>
	The euro was quoted at $1.0600 in late European trading, down  
from $1.0676 Thursday. Later, in midday trading in New York, the 
euro traded at $1.0610. 
</P>
<P>
	Other dollar rates in Europe, compared with late Thursday,  
included 110.22 Japanese yen, up from 109.08; 1.5074 Swiss francs, 
up from 1.4955; 1.4896 Canadian dollars, down from 1.4927. 
</P>
<P>
	The British pound was quoted at $1.6040, down from $1.6077.  
</P>
<P>
	In midday trading in New York, the dollar bought 109.98 yen, and  
the pound was worth $1.6038. 
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no  
longer traded separately, though they remain in use. Based on euro 
rates, the dollar is worth 1.8451 German marks, up from 1.8320; 
6.1883 French francs, up from 6.1442; 2.0790 Dutch guilders, up 
from 2.0642; 1,826.67 Italian lire, up from 1,813.67. 
</P>
<P>
	Gold closed in London at $254.00 bid per troy ounce, down from  
$254.50 on Thursday. In Zurich the bid price was $254.05, down from 
$254.65. Gold rose $1.60 in Hong Kong to close at $255.45. 
</P>
<P>
	Silver closed in London at $5.13 bid per troy ounce, down from  
$5.16. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
