<HEADLINE> Horse Owner Recovers From Surgery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	POMONA, Calif. (AP) -- Bob Lewis, who along with his wife,  
Beverly, owns Kentucky Derby winners Charismatic and Silver Charm, 
is recovering from triple bypass heart surgery. 
</P>
<P>
	Lewis, 75, was doing well after the surgery on Thursday at  
Pomona Valley Community Hospital, Beverly Lewis said. 
</P>
<P>
	Charismatic won the Kentucky Derby and Preakness this year and  
Silver Charm won those races in 1997. Both horses lost the Belmont 
Stakes and failed to win racing's Triple Crown. 
</P>
<P>
	High Yield, a 2-year-old owned by the Lewises, is entered in the  
Hopeful Stakes at Saratoga on Saturday. The colt, trained by D. 
Wayne Lukas, was purchased for $1.05 million at the Keeneland 
Summer sale. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
