<HEADLINE> Teen Gets Right To Sue Over 'Annie' </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- The sun will come out tomorrow for Joanna  
Pacitti, who won the right to pursue a lawsuit against Macy's over 
a starring role in the Broadway musical ``Annie.'' 
</P>
<P>
	A three-judge panel of the 3rd U.S. Circuit Court of Appeals  
ruled Thursday in favor of the 15-year-old girl from Philadelphia. 
</P>
<P>
	The appeals court said she can resume the breach-of-contract  
suit she filed against the department store. She claimed she won a 
contest to star in the show but was cut from the cast two weeks 
before the scheduled opening. 
</P>
<P>
	The appeals court said a judge erred in ruling that Joanna had  
won only a chance to audition, not a guaranteed Broadway role. 
</P>
<P>
	Circuit Judge Samuel A. Alito Jr. said ``it was reasonable for  
plaintiffs to believe that Macy's offered the starring role of 
`Annie' on Broadway.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The department store had billed its heavily publicized  
nationwide audition contest as ``Macy's Search for Broadway's New 
Annie.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Tim Ray, a spokesman at Macy's flagship store in New York, had  
no comment. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
