<HEADLINE> Race Horse Owner Lewis Has Surgery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SARATOGA SPRINGS, N.Y. (AP) -- Robert Lewis, a prominent  
thoroughbred racing owner, had heart bypass surgery Thursday in 
Pomona, Calif. 
</P>
<P>
	High Yield, co-owned by Lewis and his wife Beverly, is entered  
in the Hopeful Stakes at Saratoga on Saturday. The colt, trained by 
D. Wayne Lukas, was purchased for $1.05 million at the Keeneland 
Summer sale. 
