<HEADLINE> Cubs sign Reliever Bobby Ayala </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- The Chicago Cubs signed reliever Bobby Ayala on  
Friday to a contract for the remainder of the season and recalled 
outfielder Bo Porter from Triple-A Iowa. 
</P>
<P>
	Ayala, 30, was 1-6 with a 3.68 ERA in 53 relief appearances with  
Montreal before he was released Aug. 27. He struck out 64 batters 
in 66 innings. 
</P>
<P>
	The right-hander has pitched for Cincinnati, Seattle and the  
Expos in his eight-season major league career. He has a 37-43 
career record with 59 saves and a 4.84 ERA. 
</P>
<P>
	Porter, 27, joins the Cubs for the second time. He appeared in  
five games May 9-23, going 0-for-1 at the plate. In 111 games at 
Iowa, Porter batted .292 wth 86 runs scored, 24 doubles, 27 homers 
and 64 RBIs. 
  	   	
