<HEADLINE> O'Connor Says Fate in God's Hands </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Cardinal John O'Connor, hospitalized at a cancer  
center for diagnosis of an unknown ailment, says his fate remains 
in the hands of God. 
</P>
<P>
	``Life is such a gift and after almost 80 years of living it, I  
have no sentiment so strong as gratitude,'' O'Connor wrote in his 
weekly Catholic New York newsletter. 
</P>
<P>
	``But faith is an equal gift, most particularly the faith to  
believe that one's life, everyone's life, is ultimately in the 
hands of a loving God.'' 
</P>
<P>
	O'Connor, 79, has been hospitalized since Aug. 25 at Memorial  
Sloan-Kettering Cancer Center. It is not known when he will be 
released. 
</P>
<P>
	The nature of O'Connor's ailment is also unclear. He said he  
would release results of medical tests when he receives them. 
</P>
<P>
	The cardinal has announced plans to retire as head of the New  
York Roman Catholic archdiocese when he turns 80 on Jan. 15. He has 
been cardinal of the 2.2 million-member diocese, which covers 10 
New York counties, since 1984. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
