<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Murdoch Gives $10 Mil. to Cathedral </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- A $10 million donation from News Corp.  
chairman Rupert Murdoch will be used to build a conference center 
for the $163 million Cathedral of Our Lady of the Angels, currently 
under construction. 
</P>
<P>
	The donation from the Murdoch Family Foundation was announced  
Thursday by Cardinal Roger Mahony. 
</P>
<P>
	The structures ``will serve the people of Southern California as  
a whole,'' said Murdoch, who is not Catholic. ``Cardinal Mahony's 
vision for this beautiful new cathedral and all that goes with it 
deserves everybody's support.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The 3,000-seat cathedral complex, scheduled to open in 2001,  
will include a landscaped plaza, meditation garden, conference 
center, and a 24,000-square-foot residence for Mahony, resident 
clergy and visitors. 
</P>
<P>
	The cathedral will replace tiny St. Vibiana's Cathedral, which  
was closed after suffering damage in the 1994 Northridge 
earthquake. 
</P>
<P>
	``The Murdochs have long recognized the importance of Los  
Angeles as a key city for the new century and millennium,'' Mahony 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	Murdoch's News Corp. is a worldwide media conglomerate that  
includes newspapers, the Fox television network, 20th Century Fox 
film studio and satellite networks in Europe and Asia. Through Fox 
Sports, Murdoch also owns the Los Angeles Dodgers. 
</P>
<P>
	His donation raises contributions and pledges for the cathedral  
to $136.5 million, Mahony said. 
</P>
<P>
	Two years ago, Murdoch was inducted into the Order of St.  
Gregory, a papal knighthood. His former wife is Catholic. 



  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
