<HEADLINE> Predators Sign Robitaille, Millar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- The Nashville Predators signed center  
Randy Robitaille and defenseman Craig Miller and re-signed left 
wing Patrick Cote on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	The three will join the Predators for the start of training camp  
on Saturday, general manager David Poile said. 
</P>
<P>
	Robitaille, 23, had 28 goals and 74 assists in 74 games with the  
Providence Bruins. He helped lead the team to the AHL's Calder Cup 
championship. 
</P>
<P>
	The Ottawa, Ontario, native was traded to the Atlanta Thrashers,  
then to Nashville in exchange for Denny Lambert. 
</P>
<P>
	Nashville acquired Millar, 23, from the Edmonton Oilers in  
exchange for the Predators' 1999 third-round draft selection. He 
split last season between Edmonton and the AHL's Hamilton Bulldogs. 
</P>
<P>
	Cote, 24, had a goal and two assists in 70 games in his first  
full NHL season. He was originally selected by Nashville in the 
1998 expansion draft. 
  	   	
