<HEADLINE> European Stocks Close at 4-Day High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- European stocks closed at a four-day high today,  
buoyed by a strong showing on Wall Street as inflation fears 
cooled. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow Jones Stoxx Index of 592 European companies had one of  
its biggest percentage gains this year, rising 7.13 points, or 2.3 
percent, to close at 312.32. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow Jones Euro Stoxx Index, which tracks 297 companies in  
countries that joined the single currency, closed up 7.78 points at 
327.22. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow Jones Euro Stoxx 50 Index rose 90.74 points to 3,809.11,  
while the DJ Stoxx 50 Index closed up 92.73 points at 3,744.20. 
</P>
<P>
	In domestic markets, London's FTSE 100 blue-chip index closed up  
2.2 percent to 6,332.10; Frankfurt's Xetra DAX jumped 2.8 percent 
to 5,336.22; the Paris CAC-40 index rose 2.7 percent to 4,672.37; 
Milan's MIBtel index rose 2.2 percent to 34,001.00; and Amsterdam's 
AEX index rose 2.4 percent to 578.63. 
</P>
<P>
	In London, insurers were among the best-performing blue chips,  
after National Westminster Bank said it may make an offer for Legal 
&AMP; General. 
</P>
<P>
	However, National Westminster shares were the worst blue-chip  
performers, with analysts saying that a rumored $17 billion price 
tag would be too high. The stock fell 68 pence, or 5.6 percent, to 
1,143 pence. 
</P>
<P>
	``It will be a very significant move if it happens,'' said Tim  
Dyer, head of international sales at SG Securities in London. 
``Everyone has been talking about consolidation in the financial 
sector across Europe.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Norwich Union, meanwhile, was the best performer in the FTSE  
100, with a gain of 11 percent. Analysts said Norwich may be the 
next takeover target. 
</P>
<P>
	Other European insurers that rose included Germany's Allianz,  
the biggest share in the Dow Jones Stoxx Insurance index, up 5.10 
euros at 249.00 euros in Frankfurt. Dutch-based Aegon, the second 
biggest stock in the index, rose 2.90 euros to 81.95 euros. 
</P>
<P>
	In Paris, auto makers were among the leading gainers, with  
Peugeot shares finishing 10.20 euros higher at 190.10 euros, amid 
growing optimism for the sector. 


  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
