<HEADLINE> L.A. Gunmen Hijack Armored Car </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Masked gunmen hijacked an armored car Friday  
and got away with as much as a half-million dollars. 
</P>
<P>
	Guards said they were approached by two men dressed in black  
clothing and ski masks and armed with handguns, Officer Guillermo 
Campos said. 
</P>
<P>
	``They took the keys to the truck and tied up the guards,'' he  
said. 
</P>
<P>
	The armored car was driven to an alley, where the robbers  
stuffed an estimated $300,000 to $500,000 into bags and fled. 
</P>
<P>
	It was unclear whether a guard or a robber drove the truck to  
the alley, Campos said. 
</P>
<P>
	No shots were fired and the guards were not injured, he said.  
  	   	
</P>
