<HEADLINE> McGwire Hits 53rd, 54th Homers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MILWAUKEE (AP) -- Mark McGwire hit his 53rd and 54th homers  
Friday, pulling within three homers of Sammy Sosa's major 
league-leading total. 
</P>
<P>
	The second homer, a 434-foot shot to left-center off the  
Brewers' Scott Karl in the fifth inning, tied McGwire with Mel Ott 
for 14th place on the career list with 511. He now trails Ernie 
Banks and Eddie Mathews in 12th place by one. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire hit a 3-2 pitch from Karl deep into the left-field  
bleachers in the first. His second homer scored Ray Lankford and 
put St. Louis up 3-0. 
</P>
<P>
	The first baseman has homered three times in three days after  
not hitting one since Aug. 24. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire has eight multihomer games this season and 61 in his  
career. 
  	   	
</P>
