<HEADLINE> Dow Jumps 127 in Early Trading / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is up 127  
points in today's early going. Advancers on the New York Stock 
Exchange hold a 5-1 lead over decliners. 
</P>
<P>
	The Nasdaq Composite Index is up 64 points and the S&AMP;P 500 Index  
is up 13 points. 
</P>
<P>
	Wall Street is cheering today.  
</P>
<P>
	The financial markets are reacting favorably to the latest  
unemployment news from the government. 
</P>
<P>
	The August jobless rate was down a notch to 4.2 percent, even as  
payrolls rose by just 124,000. 
</P>
<P>
	Also, a wage-inflation gauge in the report showed no cause for  
concern. 
</P>
<P>
	The report came as financial markets have been bracing for bad  
news about inflation. 
</P>
<P>
	They didn't get that bad news with today's report.  
</P>
<P>
	Bond prices are sharply higher, along with the big advance in  
stock prices. 
  	   	
