<HEADLINE> Sosa Hits No. 57 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- Sammy Sosa hit his 57th homer Friday, extending  
his major league lead over Mark McGwire and staying well head of 
his pace from a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
	Sosa hit a two-run homer to left-center off Chan Ho Park in the  
first inning of Friday's game against the Los Angeles Dodgers -- his 
14th homer in 19 games. 
</P>
<P>
	Last season, when he finished with 66, Sosa didn't connect on  
his 57th until his 141st game. Sosa's homer Friday came in the 
Cubs' 133rd game. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire entered Friday with 52 homers.  
  	   	
