<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Panthers Re-Sign Four Players </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MIAMI (AP) -- Center Viktor Kozlov and defenseman Bret Hedican  
were among four players who have signed new contracts with the 
Florida Panthers, the NHL team announced Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	Also signing were defensemen Jaroslav Spacek and Filip Kuba.  
</P>
<P>
	Details of the contracts were not disclosed. However, Kozlov and  
Hedican both signed for three more years, while Spacek got a 
two-year deal and Kuba signed for one, said Panthers general 
manager Bryan Murray. 
</P>
<P>
	Kozlov, 24, scored had 16 goals and 35 assists for 51 points in  
65 games last season to tie him for second in scoring on the team. 
The 6-foot-5, 232- pound native of Toglitti, Russia, led the 
Panthers with 209 shots. 
</P>
<P>
	Hedican, 29, is an eight-year NHL veteran who last season scored  
23 points on five goals and 18 assists with Vancouver and Florida. 
He was traded to Florida last January in a deal that also brought 
Pavel Bure and Brad Ference and a draft choice. 
</P>
<P>
	Spacek, 25, last year completed his first NHL season with the  
Panthers, scoring 15 points on three goals and 12 assists in 63 
games. The 5-foot-11, 195-pound defenseman is from Rokycany in the 
Czech Republic. 
</P>
<P>
	Kuba, 22, also from the Czech Republic, last season played in 45  
games with the Kentucky Thoroughbreds of the American Hockey 
League, before joining Florida. He played in five games with the 
Panthers, posting an assist. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
