<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-03 17:30:13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Warrant Issued for Kevorkian Asst. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BERNALILLO, N.M. (AP) -- An associate of Jack Kevorkian who is  
charged with murder in the death of a New Mexico woman failed to 
show up for his arraignment Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	A judge issued an arrest warrant for Georges Reding, 74, of  
Galesburg, Mich., after no lawyer appeared on his behalf. 
</P>
<P>
	Reding, a retired psychiatrist, is accused of giving a drug  
overdose to Donna Brennan, who died in August 1998 after suffering 
from multiple sclerosis for 20 years. An autopsy showed Brennan, 
54, died from a lethal dose of pentobarbital, a sedative. 
</P>
<P>
	Reding said in 1996 that he had witnessed five assisted suicides  
and would continue to help Kevorkian judge the mental status of 
people who sought his help in dying. He said he joined Kevorkian 
because he was ``embarrassed by the cowardice of my profession'' in 
not supporting patients who seek suicide. 
</P>
<P>
	Kevorkian, who has acknowledged helping at least 120 ailing  
people commit suicide, is serving a 10- to 25-year sentence after 
being convicted of murdering a Lou Gehrig's disease patient. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
