<HEADLINE>  Lemieux Wins Control of Penguins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PITTSBURGH (AP) -- Mario Lemieux won bankruptcy court approval  
today to take control of the Pittsburgh Penguins, making him the 
first retired player to become the owner of a major sports team for 
which he played. 
</P>
<P>
	U.S. Bankruptcy Judge Bernard Markovitz approved the deal within  
minutes of Lemieux's 9 a.m. court appearance, ending a 10-month 
