<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *Friday, Sept. 3, 1999    	

</P>
<P>
	Stocks End Higher; Dow Up 235.24  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks raced higher today after the government's  
employment report calmed fears about rising inflation and prompted 
a broad rally that included the biggest point gain in the history 
of the Nasdaq composite index. At the close of trading on Wall 
Street, the Dow Jones industrial average was up 235.24 at 
11,078.45. The Dow ended an extremely volatile week with a loss of 
11.72. Broad market measures also did well. The Nasdaq composite 
index rose 108.34 to 2,842.58, surpassing the previous high for a 
one-day point gain, 103.16, set on June 16. the Standard &AMP; Poor's 
500 rose 38.13 to 1,357.24. 

</P>
<P>
	Financial Figures  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Financial figures at the close:  
NYSE Issues:         Advances 2290  Declines  677  Unchgd  513
NYSE Volume:         646,023,090
Most Active NYSE issue:         America Online97       + 5 3/4
