<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Ga. Dad Charged in Daughter's Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	RUTLEDGE, Ga. (AP) -- A man stomped his 7-year-old foster  
daughter to death when she threw a tantrum because he wouldn't buy 
her a doll, sheriff's officials said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	Sheriff's deputies charged 35-year-old Paul Morris with murder  
and cruelty to children after an autopsy showed the girl died from 
a ruptured liver. 
</P>
<P>
	The attack happened Sunday when the Morris family had returned  
from a mall. Morris and his wife bought one of their sons football 
cleats, and the girl was upset because she wanted a doll. 
</P>
<P>
	``This is not a family that just goes out and buys a lot of  
stuff all at one time,'' said Sheron Vance, an investigator with 
the Morgan County Sheriff's Department. 
</P>
<P>
	Vance said Morris hit the unidentified girl with his fists and a  
belt. Then he stomped on her and jumped on her with both feet. 
</P>
<P>
	``He'd lost it,'' she said.  
</P>
<P>
	Morris and his wife were trying to adopt the girl, who had been  
living with the family for about five months. She had been taken 
away from her natural parents because she was born addicted to 
cocaine and had been sexually and physically abused. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
