<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Jets Receiver Out Six Weeks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. (AP) -- Wayne Chrebet, who didn't miss a  
game in his first four seasons with the New York Jets, will be 
sidelined for at least six weeks with a broken left foot. 
</P>
<P>
	Chrebet was injured in the first quarter of Friday night's 38-17  
exhibition victory over the Minnesota Vikings. He wasn't touched on 
the play, which came on the artificial turf at Giants Stadium. The 
previous preseason games at the stadium this year were held on 
grass, which was removed Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Chrebet will need surgery, in which a screw will be placed in  
the foot. He left the stadium on crutches. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's a big disappointment, because I felt I had myself in the  
best possible condition,'' said Chrebet, who had 75 receptions for 
1,083 yards and eight touchdowns last season. He also is considered 
one of the best third-down receivers in football. 
</P>
<P>
	``I was just running, I wasn't hit. All of a sudden, I felt a  
pop.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The Jets are fortunate that they have depth at the position. In  
fact, veterans Quinn Early and Dwight Stone had strong games 
against Minnesota after Chrebet was injured. 
</P>
<P>
	Without Chrebet, who made the Jets in 1995 as an undrafted free  
agent, speedy Dedric Ward will become a starter. But the Jets use 
lots of four-receiver sets, so Early should see plenty of action, 
and Stone -- whose prospects of making the team were uncertain -- 
probably will get the fourth spot. 
</P>
<P>
	``We had a little setback with Wayne,'' coach Bill Parcells  
said. ``But you've got to go on. Every team has them.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Jets quarterback Vinny Testaverde said he's already looking  
forward to Chrebet's return in October. 
</P>
<P>
	``He'll be back to help the team win a lot of games,''  
Testaverde said. ``No question, when you miss a player of this 
caliber, he will be missed a lot. We've worked together so much 
over the last year, and I will miss that.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
