<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Romanowski Issues Apology on Drugs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DENVER (AP) -- Denver Broncos linebacker Bill Romanowski, under  
investigation for obtaining a prescription drug through fraud, 
issued an apology after Friday night's exhibition game. 
</P>
<P>
	``I can't talk about any of that right now,'' Romanowski said,  
``but I apologize to my teammates, the organization and all the 
fans that support me. 
</P>
<P>
	``Hopefully, this won't affect me. Hopefully, somehow and some  
way I can get through this, that I can be ready to play next 
week.'' 
</P>
<P>
	He called the Broncos' 34-3 victory over San Francisco ``very  
much of a good break. Whenever I can go out on the field and do 
what I love to do, I have the passion for the game. It was nice. 
</P>
<P>
	``I wasn't distracted. Once I took the field I was ready to  
play.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Romanowski's coach, Mike Shanahan, said he has known about the  
potential legal problems for several weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm just disappointed it all came out without going to the  
D.A. first,'' Shanahan said. ``People will eventually see that this 
is not a serious deal. I'll be surprised if there ever is a charge. 
</P>
<P>
	``I knew about it around three weeks ago, maybe a month ago.  
We'll just have to let the courts do their job.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Romanowski could be charged with felony counts of fraud and  
deceit and conspiracy, and a misdemeanor charge of unlawful use of 
a controlled substance. 
</P>
<P>
	Douglas County sheriff's officials said Romanowski's wife,  
Julie, and another woman allegedly obtained bogus prescriptions 
from a doctor for the drug Phentermine and gave it to Romanowski 
for his personal use. 
</P>
<P>
	The drug is an appetite suppressant but also acts as a  
stimulant. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
