<HEADLINE> Prep Football Player Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	GLADWIN, Mich. (AP) -- Gerald Lane, a 15-year-old high school  
football player who ran for a touchdown, collapsed moments later 
during a football game, then died at a hospital. 
</P>
<P>
	Lane collapsed during the third quarter of Gladwin's game  
Wednesday night against Meridian and died after arriving at 
MidMichigan Medical Center. 
</P>
<P>
	Police Chief Charles Jones said Lane ran for a touchdown  
``unscathed, not even touched. He was walking out of the end zone 
and just collapsed.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The death is the second in less than a year involving an area  
athlete. In February, Billy Geiling, a freshman basketball player 
from Meridian, fell to the court and died during a game against 
Roscommon. 
</P>
<P>
	The cause of Geiling's death was ruled a rare cyst at the stem  
of his brain that cut off blood flow. 
</P>
<P>
	Gladwin County medical examiner Dr. James Sullivan planned an  
autopsy Thursday. Jones said it wasn't immediately known whether 
Lane had prior medical problems. 
</P>
<P>
	Gladwin athletic department and school officials were  
unavailable for comment. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
